In article <1993Sep25.021404.1@mcclb0> huff@mcclb0.med.nyu.edu (Edward J. Huff) writes:
> Security by obscurity is just another way of saying you can't read
> the message unless you know the key.

No. There's a subtle difference. A cryptosystem turns into ``security by 
obscurity'' only if _the key can't be changed_.

---Dan
